# Normalize line endings for all text files on commit; Git still checks
# files out using each platform's native convention (CRLF on Windows via
# core.autocrlf), but the blobs stored in the repo are always LF. This
# repo has repeatedly hit whole-file-rewrite diff noise from files whose
# line endings didn't match this convention when committed from a
# different environment (see PROGRESS.md's 2026-07-16 through 2026-07-19
# check-in notes) — this file makes the policy explicit and repo-tracked
# instead of depending on each contributor's local core.autocrlf value.
* text=auto

# Never convert line endings for genuinely binary assets.
*.png binary
*.jpg binary
*.jpeg binary
*.gif binary
*.ico binary
*.webp binary
*.woff binary
*.woff2 binary
*.ttf binary
*.eot binary
*.db binary
*.sqlite binary
*.zip binary
